# Combat System Rules

The combat model is the heart of Mythora. Do not change these rules without explicit approval.

## Battle Loop

```text
Battle Starts
  -> Player Turn Begins
  -> Moves Refresh
  -> Player Swaps Tiles
  -> Matches Generate Resources
  -> Matches Generate AP
  -> Player Uses Skills
  -> Moves Reach Zero or Player Ends Turn
  -> Enemy Turn
  -> Status Effects Resolve
  -> Next Player Turn
```

## Tile Colors

| Tile | Resource |
|------|----------|
| Red | Attack Energy |
| Blue | Mana |
| Green | Healing Energy |
| Yellow | Shield Energy |
| Purple | Ultimate Energy |

## Matching

- Matching does not directly damage enemies.
- Matching generates resources.
- Matching generates AP according to balance rules.
- Every swap consumes 1 Move.
- Invalid swaps should not consume Moves unless explicitly configured.

## Moves

- Moves are the puzzle action budget.
- Moves refresh at the start of each player turn.
- Moves do not carry over by default.
- Hero passives, equipment, buffs, debuffs, and bosses may modify Moves.

## AP

- AP is combat stamina.
- AP persists until spent.
- AP is not automatically restored to full each turn.
- AP has a max capacity per hero/team.
- AP is earned through puzzle performance.

## Skills

Every skill must define:
- resource costs
- AP cost
- target rules
- effect list
- validation
- optional cooldown
- animation cue

A skill cannot execute if:
- required resources are missing
- required AP is missing
- target is invalid
- caster is dead/stunned/silenced when relevant

## Enemy Turn

Enemy actions should be deterministic enough to test.

Enemy actions may:
- attack
- buff
- debuff
- summon
- alter board tiles
- add hazards
- trigger boss mechanics

Do not implement enemy behavior directly inside UI widgets.
